quick , easy , heartwarming i met ms. holt in ... ( basis for her fictional town of moon ) . she is like her characters ... down-to-earth , witty , and honest . as a twenty-seven year old teacher , i read this novel for three reasons : its setting ... i 've read her other novels and loved them , and to find new reading material for recommendation to my students . i was not disappointed . jaynell and her family are easy to identify with , easy to follow , and easy to love . the story line is not difficult and the messages ring all too true ! pick this one up , you wo n't stop 'till the end